# FlashQuery Macro Testing Framework — gitignore policy
#
# This framework's authoritative artifacts (test cases, coverage matrix,
# failure-triage records, golden source) are checked in. Scaffolding artifacts
# from agent-driven development and ephemeral run outputs are gitignored.
#
# See _Golden-Spec-Compliance-Audit.md + the framework requirements doc §9.4 / §9.6
# for the rationale behind the committed surfaces.

# ─── Negate parent gitignore rule for `coverage/` ──────────────────────────
# The repo root .gitignore ignores `coverage/` (intended for nyc/istanbul
# output). That unanchored rule would match our coverage matrix directory.
# Per §9.4 the coverage matrix MUST be committed (manifest.ts, coverage.json,
# MTF_COVERAGE.md, MTF_INTERACTIONS.md), so we re-include it here.
!coverage/
!coverage/**

# ─── Fresh-cadence generated tests ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Per §5.5 fresh mode: tests generated on each CI run, never committed.
cases-fresh/

# ─── Scaffolding / debugging artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
# Convention: anything prefixed `_` at the top level of the framework is a
# scratch/debug file (smoke runners, probes, intermediate checks). Real
# framework code uses descriptive names.
_*.ts
_*.js

# ─── macOS / editor cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# ─── Logs / temp ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
tmp/
.cache/
